The timing of their decision does mean that Suarez can play Barcelona’s last pre-season friendly against Mexican club FC Léon de Guanjuato on Monday and be presented to supporters.

The lifting of the ban on non-official matches means he can also play for Uruguay in forthcoming friendlies against Japan and Korea although the fact that he definitely misses the Copa America, to be played in Chile next year, will perhaps make his involvement in those games unlikely.

The Suarez camp had high hopes on Thursday morning but there was also an expectation that getting any FIFA ruling over-turned was going to be impossible. Suarez can at least start feeling like a footballer again. He does not have to go running in the Pyrenees or in disguise along the beach of his new home on the Costa Brava.

